# Week 13: Must-Win Scenarios

## Required Inputs
- `{sport}` - Selected sport (NFL/NBA/MLB/NHL/Soccer)
- `{league_name}` - Name of the fantasy league
- `{period_number}` - Current week/gameweek
- `{period_name}` - Week/Gameweek/Period based on sport
- `{selected_tone}` - User's chosen tone
- `{uploaded_data}` - Current standings and remaining schedules

## Prompt Template

Write 200-word elimination scenarios in {sport} fantasy for {league_name} in {selected_tone} tone.

REAL-WORLD CONTEXT: Reference actual {sport} elimination scenarios:
- Compare to real {sport} teams facing elimination
- Mention actual "win and in" games happening
- Reference famous elimination games in {sport} history
- Use real playoff-clinching scenarios as examples

[IF BANTER]: Playful pressure - "No pressure, but lose and your season's over. Sleep tight!"
[IF BRUTAL]: Harsh reality - "Win or go home, and based on your roster, start packing"
[IF PROFESSIONAL]: Clear scenarios - "Team A clinches with win + Team B loss OR..."
[IF CINEMATIC]: Do or die drama - "Everything has led to this moment... survive or perish"
[IF CASUAL]: Straightforward - "Here's what needs to happen for you to make playoffs"

Sport-specific elimination references:
[IF NFL]: "Week 17 win-and-in scenarios"
[IF NBA]: "Play-in tournament pressure"
[IF MLB]: "Game 163 vibes"
[IF NHL]: "Final night of the season chaos"
[IF Soccer]: "Final day relegation battle intensity"

Detail exact scenarios for each bubble team, make the stakes clear.
Compare pressure to real {sport} elimination games.

## Key Elements
- List each bubble team's scenario
- Reference real {sport} elimination games
- Include win-and-in situations
- Explain tiebreaker situations

## Version History
- v1.0 - Must-win scenario breakdown
- v2.0 - Added multi-sport support and real-world integration
